title: Psych: The Movie
description_full: The movie begins three years after the events of the Psych series finale. On a dilapidated boat in the harbor, there appears to be a black market flea market going on including guns, jewelry, etc. Shawn Spencer (James Roday Rodriguez) is dressed up in a costume as Hagrid from Harry Potter and is rummaging through items on a table. He is noticed by El Proveedor (Robert La Sardo), the criminal fence running the sale. El Proveedor questions Shawn as to what he is doing. After Shawn responds with silly answers, El Proveedor's henchmen pull guns on Shawn. This causes all the other criminals on the boat to all pull guns on each other. During the confusion caused by this, Shawn grabs a sack of stolen jewelry and makes a run for it. Shawn uses the beard from the costume to zip-line off the boat. El Proveedor and his henchmen chase Shawn. Once Shawn makes it to an alley and doesn't see his pursuers behind him anymore, he searches the sack of jewelry but doesn't find what he was searching for. His pursuers catch up to him, so Shawn dumps the jewelry onto the ground and runs through the back door of a building. The building is an office building and the workplace of Burton Guster "Gus" (Dule' Hill). Shawn finds Gus' office and hides under his desk. Gus, who is currently sitting at his desk eating lunch, remarks about not giving Shawn permission to borrow his Hagrid costume. Shawn asks Gus to pull the fire alarm and for half of the sandwich Gus is eating. Gus walks out into the hallway and tells Shawn's pursuers the man they are chasing got onto the elevator. They head toward the lobby thinking Shawn is leaving the building. Gus returns to his office to see Shawn has disappeared and so has the sandwich Gus was eating.Juliet O'Hara (Maggie Lawson) is sitting in her work vehicle when her partner Sam Sloane (Sam Huntington) returns to the car with two coffees complaining how far he had to go to find a place that had any of the nut milks. Juliet tells Sam they nabbed 8 suspects on their sting operation where they have left a cell phone and shopping bag unattended at a table outside a nearby cafe and arrest anyone they witness try to steal the items. They are about to end for the day when they see the items get picked up by another suspect. They decide to get this one more, and Juliet gets out of the car. The suspect sees Juliet, whose police badge is visible on her belt, and turns around and runs. Juliet seemingly knows the likely intended escape route of the suspect and walks around the back of the building to an alley where the suspect almost runs right into her. Juliet is surprised when the suspect looks up, and Juliet sees it is Iris Vick (Emma Tremblay), Chief Vick's daughter. Iris begs Juliet to let her go and puts the stolen items on the ground. Juliet tells her to run away. When Sam catches up to Juliet, he seems to know something is weird about the situation but doesn't push the issue.Later that night, Sam walks into his apartment and realizes his alarm system has already been disarmed. An intruder starts talking to Sam, who recognizes the voice as "Billy." The Thin White Duke "Duke" (Zachary Levi) remarks he never really looked like a Billy and to call him the Duke. Sam makes a joke about the new name and look, smashes a gingerbread house on the table next to him, and pulls out the gun that was hidden inside pointing it at Duke. Duke laughs and tells Sam he no longer works alone. Duke's two partners, Heather Rockrear (Ashley Fliehr) and the Black Gentleman Ninja "BGN" (Nathan Mitchell) as they are eventually named by Shawn and Gus, enter from another room behind Sam pointing guns at him. Sam tries to negotiate, but Heather and BGN shoot Sam.The next morning, Juliet shows up at the Chief's house to talk about the situation involving her daughter, Iris. Chief Karen Vick (Kirsten Nelson) says she just has to get her husband off to the airport, and then they can ride into work together. Once Karen is out of the room, Iris comes downstairs and begs Juliet not to tell her mom. Iris says she was put up to the theft by these horrible girls at school who bully everyone. Juliet agrees not to tell Karen and has Iris promise to call Juliet if she any more problems with those girls or anyone else. They pinky promise right as Karen comes back into the room who comments she is jealous of how close Iris and Juliet are. When Juliet and Karen get in the car, Juliet tells Karen never mind about what she wanted to talk to her about. This prompts Karen to say she knows what it was about, Juliet's relationship with Shawn. Juliet says that's not it, and she's not in a rush to get married. Karen comments how she notices Juliet doesn't wear an engagement ring despite being engaged to Shawn. Juliet then gets a call informing her Sam has been shot.El Proveedor is interrogating the man who came on the boat right before Shawn to find out Shawn's identity, but the man doesn't know anything. One of El Proveedor's henchmen comes in saying they found something on the beard dropped by Shawn after zip-lining off the boat. Inside the beard is a sewn in patch that says, "Property of Burton Guster." El Proveedor tells his henchmen to find Burton Guster.Gus enters the Psych office which is underground in an alley in Chinatown. When Gus enters, Shawn comments how he just finished decorating the place to match the shop from the 30th anniversary edition of Gremlins. Gus comments that the problem is the name of the business which is "psychphrancisco." Shawn disagrees and tells Gus they have a case. Shawn tells Gus that Juliet's partner Sam has been shot and is in the ICU. Gus expresses surprise the police would hire them for the case. Shawn admits they haven't actually been hired by the police yet but plans to get them on the case. He convinces Gus to go by promising to stop at every Cinnabon between the office and the hospital, and they will be done in time to go to a planetarium party Gus wants to attend later that night.Shawn and Gus arrive at the hospital. Sam's hospital room is filled with cops. Shawn and Gus stand in the back when Karen starts to give a briefing. Shawn and Gus start talking which gets Karen's attention, and she asks who is back there. Shawn and Gus move in front of all the cops and say they are there to pay their respects to Sam. Karen continues with her briefing. She says the only thing that was taken from Sam's apartment is his dongle, a security device that allows access to confidential police files. Shawn childishly takes dongle to be a penis metaphor, and after making inappropriate comments and not being able to control his laughter when the dongle is described as purple and curved, Juliet takes Shawn and Gus aside and basically kicks them out of the hospital saying they are not allowed to help with the investigation.Once outside the hospital, Shawn and Gus are discreetly called to the side of the building by Nick Conforth (Ralph Macchio). Nick is an instructor at the Santa Barbara Police Academy that Shawn and Gus had to attend during a previous episode. Nick says he came to see Sam who he knows when he was Sam's instructor at the academy until Juliet kicked him out of the hospital too. Nick says that Juliet is hiding something, but Shawn and Gus doubt him. Nick says that Sam called him yesterday saying no one could be trusted, especially not Juliet. Sam told Nick he kept getting phone calls talking about The Crimes of Juliet. Sam traced the number to a specific cellphone tower, but Sam was shot before he had the chance to check it out. Since Nick is an instructor because he is terrified to work in the field as an officer, he asks Shawn and Gus to check it out.When Shawn and Gus find the cellphone tower, the only thing anywhere nearby is a mental hospital. Dusk sets in as Shawn and Gus drive up to the locked gate of the mental hospital. A sign on the front gate says the hospital has been closed for two years. They approach the hospital while hearing weird animal noises which Shawn realizes is Gus playing Pokemon Go on his phone. Shawn notices someone has tapped into the power lines and ran a cable into the hospital. Shawn and Gus enter through a submarine looking door into a dark hallway where they see a light at the end. An attack dog chases them back through the door. Shawn realizes by the dog's collar that he is a rescue. He enters the door again and tries to calm the dog using a trick he saw on the Dog Whisperer. The trick doesn't work, but then Shawn notices Gus eating beef jerky. Shawn makes Gus give him the jerky to give to the dog. Once Shawn gives the jerky to the dog, the dog calms down and likes Shawn letting him pet him. Shawn and Gus make their way down the hallway to a room full of computer monitors. They see Sam's dongle plugged into the computer and see various police files open on the screens. Shawn is scrolling through the documents when they see a manifesto pop up called The Crimes of Juliet O'Hara. Shawn and Gus hear a door slam shut and hide. Duke, Heather, and BNG walk into the room. Duke realizes someone has been there and orders the other two to do a perimeter search. Duke sees the manifesto up on the screen and says they will have to speed up their plan. Shawn and Gus run out of the hospital, but then Shawn runs back into the hospital and back out again with the attack dog in his arms. Shawn and Gus get into the Driver's Ed car they stole in the series finale that has a steering wheel and pedals on both the driver's and passenger's side of the car and take forever to turn around as they are both trying to drive.Karen wakes up. She looks out her bedroom window and notices lights in her garage. She opens the garage to find Shawn, Gus, and the dog. Shawn said they are there to gift Karen the dog and tells her about the mental hospital. When the dog starts barking at Karen, she does the trick from the Dog Whisperer tried by Shawn earlier, but it works this time and the dog stops barking and lays down. Shawn tells Karen he tried to contact Juliet to tell her about the hospital as well, but Juliet hasn't responded.Shawn, Gus, and Karen all go to the mental hospital. Shawn leads them to the same room they were in earlier with all the monitors and Sam's dongle, but the room is now completely empty. They hear someone coming. It's Juliet. She came to help Shawn and Gus, who she knew were there because of all the traffic violations they committed while speeding away from the hospital. Juliet yells at Shawn and Gus for getting involved in the case after she told them not to and tells them to leave and go to their planetarium party.Shawn and Gus enter the planetarium party. Gus notices a girl across the room and starts talking about approaching her. Before he has the chance, the girl makes eye contact and starts approaching Gus which makes Gus uncomfortable. They introduce themselves. Selene (Jazmyn Simon) then invites Gus to look through the telescope with her.Juliet tells Karen she may have an idea who is behind everything, but she needs to pursue the lead alone. Karen says no, but Juliet asks Karen to trust her. Karen gives her 24 hours, but Juliet says she'll only need 12 if Sam wakes up so she's going to the hospital.Back at the party, Selene is looking through the telescope saying that's where the 9th planet would be if the telescope were powerful enough. Gus laughs and then corrects her telling her Pluto is located somewhere else in the sky. She questions him as to why she would be showing him Pluto and says she is talking about Eris. Gus laughs saying the dwarf planet Eris is stupid and that Pluto will always be the 9th planet. They argue back and forth with each other until Selene starts kissing Gus. Gus seems uncomfortable with Selene being so aggressive and storms off. Shawn yells after Gus that this is probably his best chance ever of finding a wife.At the hospital, Juliet walks out of the elevator. As she approaches Sam's room, she sees various hospital staff running around tending to two police officers who have been shot outside Sam's room. Inside Sam's room, she sees a doctor using a defibrillator on Sam who is dead. Then we see Duke's partner Heather wearing pink scrubs getting onto the elevator.At the morgue, Medical Examiner Dr. Butterfly McMillan (Julianna Guill) pulls the sheet over Sam's face and apologizes to Juliet, Shawn, and Gus for the missing report as her assistant must have misplaced it. The assistant comes out of the back, and it is Woody Strode (Kurt Fuller), the former Santa Barbara Medical Examiner. Everyone is surprised to see each other. Woody explains he had gotten the position of Head Medical Examiner for the state of California, but he got fired for leaving a chili dog inside a cadaver and then opening the cadaver back up to retrieve the chili dog. Juliet refocuses Butterfly who says the cause of death was asphyxiation. Then Selene shows up out of no where screaming for Gus before walking into the morgue. Gus asks Selene if she is there because she works there. Selene says no, and that she saw Gus' Instagram post about going to the morgue so she stopped by. Gus takes Selene into the hallway to talk. Selene cuts Gus off before he can say anything telling him she took his business card and checked him out. Selene says she likes everything she found, so she chooses Gus. Butterfly tries to get back to what she was talking about when she finds something inside Sam's stomach. Gus tells Selene she doesn't even know him which prompts her to go off on a long tangent about all the things she knows about him including things from his childhood. While Gus starts telling her all the things she shouldn't be doing, Shawn points out to Woody that Gus has done all those things before. Woody points out that Gus is getting "Gused" which is why he doesn't like it. Selene tells Gus his points are completely fair, leaves him her dating "resume," and gives him a Fluffernutter sandwich which she found out from Gus' mother is his favorite. Butterfly is finally able to retrieve the item from Sam's stomach which is Sam's dongle. They plug the dongle into a computer, but the only thing still on it is the manifesto "The Crimes of Juliet O'Hara."Shawn and Gus are walking back to their office. Shawn is talking about how it worries him not knowing what is going on with Juliet. When they enter the office, they are grabbed by El Proveedor's henchmen. El Proveedor comments that people that steal from him usually run further away. Gus argues that Shawn didn't mean to steal and was just working a case. El Proveedor threatens Shawn to tell him who the client is. After some reluctance, Shawn admits he himself is the client, and he is looking for the engagement ring he gave Juliet that was immediately stolen right after proposing. Gus flips out on Shawn saying Shawn has been ruining their business the last three years looking for this ring. El Proveedor asks Shawn if he has considered whether Shawn is using the ring as an excuse for his fear of change. El Proveedor tells his men to kill Shawn and Gus. Shawn mentions he is a psychic detective which prompts El Proveedor to make Shawn predict his future. Shawn tells El Proveedor of three predictions, one involving a bus and curb, one involving a tax issue, and that he must lay off the salt. El Proveedor says he'll see how the predictions play out and then decide whether to kill Shawn and Gus.Shawn and Gus go to Shawn and Juliet's apartment where Juliet is sitting on the couch looking at a wall of paperwork she has taped up. She apologizes to Shawn for how she's been acting and asks for his help. The paperwork on the wall is the paperwork from all the cases mentioned in the manifesto. Juliet implies there is some truth to the manifesto. While all of the suspects in those cases are guilty, she has done some things of which she's not proud. Juliet says she's "fudged" some rules and skipped some protocols to put these bad guys away. Shawn reassures her she is fine as she did not do anything illegal and that he has lied for years about being psychic just to put bad guys away. Shawn then looks over the paperwork on the wall using his hyper-observance taught to him by his father and determines it is not any of the suspects from the cases. It's the confidential informant from all the cases, Billy McGoldrick (Duke). Juliet says he informed on all of the suspects from those cases. Gus asks what his beef is then. Juliet says she still sent him to jail. Gus mentions that Billy must be the person following Juliet which prompts Shawn to remember a surveillance picture he'd seen of Juliet on the computer screen at the mental hospital. Remembering the picture, Shawn realizes Juliet had her house keys in her hand meaning she must have been close to the door of their apartment building. Shawn goes to the window and looks down at exactly where Juliet was when the picture was taken. Shawn realizes it was from the opposite side, so the picture must have been taken from a building across the street. As Shawn looks up at the building across the street, he sees Duke looking out and makes eye contact with him.Shawn, Gus, and Juliet all run downstairs and out into the street. Duke runs outside as well. Juliet pulls her gun on him telling him to freeze, and Duke runs back inside. Shawn, Gus, and Juliet follow the Duke inside and a shootout occurs. Duke throws down his gun saying while he would love to kill Juliet, he has promised he would not do that yet. He backs away while Juliet holds him at gun point until he is close enough to roll back through a doorway and then hits a button causing a metal door to slam down shut between Juliet and him.Back in Shawn and Juliet's apartment, Gus is about to eat something when Shawn calls him over to the window to look at a weird looking guy trying to enter the building. When the weird guy looks up, Shawn realizes it is his father, Henry Spencer (Corbin Bernsen). Shawn is surprised to see his father dressed like a hipster. Juliet comes home and is surprised to see Henry. Henry tells her he wasn't going to stay home when someone is targeting her. Juliet doesn't want anyone else to be in danger.Juliet and Shawn are in bed talking. Shawn is trying to reassure her, but Juliet has difficulty accepting the help. She steps out onto the balcony and calls her former partner Carlton Lassiter (Timothy Omundson) on FaceTime. Carlton says he spoke with Henry and is aware of the situation. Juliet tells him it's all her fault as she "colored out of the lines." Carlton offers to come from Santa Barbara to help, but Juliet tells him she can handle it.Shawn wakes up after hearing a noise. He walks past a sleeping Gus on the couch and goes into the kitchen where he sees someone from behind squatting down. The person stands up and turns around. It's Mary Lightly (Jimmi Simpson). Shawn now knows he is dreaming since Mary was murdered by the serial killer Mr. Yin in a previous episode. Shawn confirms this by looking back into the living room where he says a pony that tells him to stay golden. Mary asks Shawn how his girl is doing, and Shawn tells him how he's worried he's going to lose her if he doesn't find the ring soon. Mary says he knows what Shawn needs. Mary pulls out a guitar and starts singing Allison Road by the Gin Blossoms. Shawn joins in singing along with a holographic Princess Leia dressed Juliet and Prince dressed Gus. Shawn is then woken up by Henry yelling at him to get up.At Karen's house, Iris walks outside when her cell phone starts to ring. It's Mischa, one of the mean girls from school. Iris answers the phone and tells Mischa off. Iris walks around the corner where Duke is standing and compliments her on her courage standing up to Mischa on the phone. Iris says thanks, but she does not talk to strangers. As Iris starts walking away, Duke comes up behind her holding a Chloroform soaked cloth over her mouth causing her to pass out.Karen is at the harbor in front of Duke. Duke remarks he's surprised Karen arrived before Juliet considering Juliet is so close to Iris. Juliet shows up with Shawn, Gus, Henry, and Woody right behind. Duke complains as Juliet was supposed to come alone and has to call in on the radio about the additional people. Whomever Duke talks to on the radio says everyone can come as it was not unexpected for everyone to show up. Duke has everyone put any guns they have in one boat and then get into another boat. Duke then gets into the boat and takes them all to Alcatraz. They all walk into a cell block. At the end, a spotlight comes on on a balcony where Duke, Heather, and BGN are all standing. Karen asks what Duke has done with Iris.Duke tells Karen to be quiet and goes off on a tangent. Duke mentions his job is done and is now going to introduce tonight's headliner. He starts to go off on another tangent, but is then shot in the back and falls over. From behind walks out Allison Cowley (Mena Suvari) who was Mr. Yin's assistant and arrested by Juliet the same night Mr. Yin was killed. Shawn then realizes the significance of his dream and the song in it, Allison Road. Shawn starts talking about the dream and all the details causing Allison to shoot more bullets into Duke's body on the ground to shut him up and regain everyone's attention. Shawn asks Allison why she just shot her partner. Allison says Duke was no longer useful. While Allison is going on about her plan, Gus points out to Shawn that the cheese cloth used by the workers doing the restoration project workers off to the side is not hanging straight down the way it should be giving them a possible hint about where to go to find Iris. Allison gets annoyed at Shawn and Gus not paying attention. Juliet asks Allison what she wants. Allison says she wants a do over as Juliet arrested her on the night she was supposed to be taking over as a serial killer for Mr. Yin. As Allison is pondering aloud her overuse of similes, Shawn points out the clue about the cheese cloth to Karen. Allison tells Karen that Iris is hidden somewhere in the building and explosives are involved. Allison tells everyone other then Karen and Juliet they will have to fight her colleagues, Heather and BGN.Karen runs off to start looking for Iris. Allison says go and turns off the spotlight that is on them. Juliet runs off the opposite direction of Karen and starts looking for Iris and is followed by Shawn and Gus. Gus starts off in a different direction and Shawn follows. Gus says he is trying to find a way outside to get to the lighthouse to signal for help. He pushes various buttons on the wall, one of which seems to open a big metal door. Once the door opens, the BGN walks out and politely shakes hands with Shawn and Gus commenting that he will be dismantling them shortly. BGN then pulls out a sword.Juliet walks into a room where Allison is. Allison comments that Juliet still has no ring on her finger. Juliet ponders aloud why everyone keeps saying that and then the two women start to fight. Henry and Woody are walking down a hallway. As they reach an opening, Heather punches Woody in the nose. Henry starts talking to her but is cut off by Heather grabbing him, kneeing him, and throwing him to the ground. Heather then starts attacking Henry and Woody in a kind of WWE style assault. Shawn and Gus are backing up in a cell block amazed as BGN does fancy moves with the sword. Karen finds Iris locked in a jail cell with her hands tied behind her back and her mouth duct taped. There is a note hanging inside the cell that says "What about the key?." Karen tells Iris not to worry and goes off looking for the key.Shawn and Gus are still backing up and talking as BGN continues. Gus comments how he shouldn't have rejected Selene, and Shawn comments how he shouldn't let the ring missing hinder his life with Juliet. Then BGN stops as he is ready to fight. Shawn and Gus scream and run away. Juliet and Allison continue fighting. Juliet notices a shotgun hanging up on the wall. As she tries to go for it, Allison stops her and throws her into a glass table. Woody is laying under a table. Henry is laying on top of the table. Heather is standing on another table nearby and readies to jump onto the two men. As she prepares to jump, Henry takes the scarf from around his neck and swings it like a whip around Heather's leg. Henry pulls the scarf causing Heather to fall back off of the table. Henry picks up a folded chair and hits Heather with it twice. Then Karen walks in, picks up a folded chair, and hits Heather knocking her unconscious.While Juliet lays on the ground recovering from going through the glass table, Allison starts talking about everything they have in common except one thing as she gets the shotgun off the wall. Juliet points out that Allison is a sociopath who doesn't feel empathy, and Allison agrees that was the one thing. Juliet starts talking about another difference and then goes into a long speech about how she supports Shawn including his office location, his weird name for the business, his designing the office to replicate Gremlins, etc. Juliet says the point of it all is there is a martial arts gym next door to the office where she learned what a "kip-up" (a martial arts move where a person transitions from a laying down position to a stand up position) is. Juliet then kicks Allison and does a kip-up to get to her feet quickly. Juliet then hits Allison again and throws Allison onto the ground while also taking the shotgun from her. Allison then does a kip-up but is immediately hit in the head with the shotgun by Juliet. Karen then comes in saying they need a key. Juliet signals for her to search Allison who is laying on the ground unconscious. Karen does and finds a key ring full of keys. Karen then runs out of the room back toward Iris.Shawn and Gus run into a hallway where they see Henry with BGN behind him holding a garrote around Henry's neck. Shawn comments to Gus "Gus as a table." Gus comments that it never works, but Shawn says it did work once. Gus then turns around and runs out of the room. Karen and Juliet run to the cell Iris is locked in. Juliet warns Karen not to unlock the door yet as Allison warned about explosives. They look inside the door and see a bomb with a timer counting down. Karen tells Iris to try and move toward the back of the cell. Shawn saying silly things to distract BGN while Gus crawls in from a door behind BGN positioning himself on his hands and knees right behind BGN as a "table." Shawn gives Henry a hint about the table, so Henry elbows BGN and steps away as Shawn pushes BGN over the Gus table. BGN falls back over Gus gracefully landing on his feet perfectly and gets into a ready fighting position. Shawn and Gus comedically get into ready fighting positions of their own, but then Woody comes out from behind BGN and cocks a shotgun telling him to freeze. Henry walks over to Woody taking the shotgun from him as he is much more proficient with firearms as a retired cop.Back at Iris' cell, the bomb timer is down to 27 seconds. Karen tells Juliet to run away to safety, but she doesn't. Iris finally manages to pull her hands free of the rope they were tied with and pulls the duct tape off of her mouth. Now finally able to talk, Iris tells Karen not to pull the wire. Iris goes on to say there's a code to disarm the bomb, and the code is the date Allison got arrested. After a second, Juliet gets excited remembering the date and punches in the code disarming the bomb with 5 seconds left. Karen asks why Juliet remembers the date, and Juliet says it was kind of a big night for her. Karen unlocks the cell and runs in to hug Iris just as Shawn, Gus, Henry, and Woody arrive outside the cell.They arrive back at the harbor. Henry says he's going to leave as he has a unicycling class that starts soon, but then Henry says screw it and that he is going to go fishing. Selene runs up saying hi to Gus and gives him flowers. Gus hands Shawn the flowers and tells Selene the Fluffernutter sandwich she made him was the best one he's had in his life. He says he is open to dating, but she has to let him be the "cheetah" meaning the one to be more of the aggressor in the relationship. Selene says no problem then grabs Gus and starts kissing him. Gus points out that is not letting him be the cheetah, so she pretends to cower and Gus "pounces" on her.Someone calls Shawn's name. Shawn turns to see El Proveedor and his two henchmen approaching. El Proveedor tells Shawn all of Shawn's premonitions about his future came true. Gus is shocked and asks El Proveedor if he is being serious. El Proveedor says yes, and then a cut away scene starts. The first one shows Buzz McNab (Sage Brocklebank) dressed up posing as an IRS agent telling El Proveedor his tax issue has been resolved. Next McNab is dressed up as Santa Claus and stops El Proveedor from stepping into the street getting hit by a bus. Finally, McNab is dressed up in a different disguise at a restaurant sitting at the table next to El Proveedor. McNab asks to borrow the salt from El Proveedor's table but pretends to have a heart attack before getting it and advises them to heed the warning.El Proveedor says he appreciates Shawn's psychic gift, and in return, he has a gift for Shawn. El Proveedor reaches inside his jacket prompting Shawn and Gus to think he's about to pull out a gun. But instead, he pulls out a ring box. Juliet walks up next to Shawn as El Proveedor hands Shawn the ring box. Inside is the engagement ring that was stolen right after Shawn proposed to Juliet. Shawn and Juliet are in shock. Shawn thanks El Proveedor and says he's ready to get married. Shawn starts spouting out some crazy wedding ideas involving volcanoes and castles and other crazy things. Juliet says she doesn't need that or anything special and that she never has. She says they should just go to Vegas now and get married. El Proveedor interjects to let them know he's ordained and can marry them. Selene tries to step next to Juliet saying she can be the maid of honor, but Karen comes up behind telling her that is not going to happen. Gus starts crying, so Shawn tells him he needs Gus to pull it together so he can give his best man speech. BGN, who is handcuffed and being escorted by an officer, stops and offers them his sincerest congratulations. Shawn thanks him and comments "that's just a good dude." The camera pans out as El Proveedor starts the ceremony with the typical "Dearly beloved..."In the psychphrancisco office, Shawn is pretending to have his finger stuck in a glass fish mouth. Gus tells Shawn to stop goofing off and find his passport as Juliet and Selene are already at the airport checked in and waiting for them. Shawn finds it and then picks up a pineapple asking if he should slice it up for the road. Shawn is wearing a #TeamGrimmie shirt. Gus asks Shawn if he and Juliet are sure they are okay with Gus and Selene coming along on their honeymoon. Shawn says they are sure. They hear what sounds like gunshots outside. Gus asks if they should be worried, but Shawn says it's probably just firecrackers since they are in Chinatown. Just then, Juliet's brother, Ewan O'Hara (John Cena), comes down the steps and into their office. Holding a wrapped gift. Ewan congratulates Shawn for finally making a honest woman out of his sister. Gus worriedly asks what Ewan is doing there as Shawn and Gus know Ewan is or was a black ops operative for the government. Ewan says he is chilling as he closes the door and barricades the door with a big piece of metal. Ewan asks if there is a back door to the office and gives Shawn a wedding present. Ewan then asks if they have a Kevlar vest or lead shield he could borrow. Shawn says they are about to leave to go to the airport to go to Jamaica for his honeymoon. Ewan makes small talk commenting on the Gremlins design of the office while suspiciously looking outside the window. All of a sudden, a helicopter can be heard outside and a voice over a loud speaker telling Ewan to come out with his hands up. Ewan tells them not to worry as this is all about him. Then green rifle laser sights start shining through the front window. The voice over the loud speaker then says for "Shawn Spencer and associate" to come out as well. Ewan tells them they are now involved, and Gus angrily comments being referred to as "associate" as he pays the rent for the office. Ewan hurries them toward the back door. Ewan sees Shawn is not holding the present and tells Shawn he is going to need it. Ewan throws a tear gas grenade on the ground while Shawn runs back to grab the present. As Shawn gets the present and starts running back toward the office back door, the operatives outside the office start shooting into the office. Ewan warns Shawn not to break the case of the present or drop it as they run out the back door. Gus asks Ewan if the present if really a wedding gift, and Ewan tells Gus it's the thought that counts. The End.

title: A Cinderella Story: Christmas Wish
description_full: Kat Decker could really use a Christmas miracle. The aspiring singer-songwriter may have big dreams, but she has even bigger problems. Treated like a servant by her vain stepmother and self-involved stepsisters, Kat is forced into a demoralizing job as a singing elf at billionaire Terrence Wintergarden's Santa Land. But there is one bright spot to the job: Nick, the handsome new Santa at the tree lot and charms his way into her heart. When Kat gets invited to the prestigious Wintergarden Christmas Gala, her step-family is determined to prevent her from attending and snag their own invitation. Could an attentive dog, a loyal BFF and a sprinkling of holiday magic help turn things around for Kat? Join Laura Marano (Disney's Austin and Ally), Gregg Sulkin (Marvel's Runaways) and Isabella Gomez (One Day at a Time) in this modern-day re-imagining of the cherished classic, featuring original music and holiday favorites.

title: Redbad
description_full: 700 AD. Northern Europe is divided into two worlds: the Frisians, Saxons and Danes live above the rivers, below the rivers live the Franks. They want to achieve what even the Romans did not succeed: conquer all of Europe. They put in a new weapon to enslave the Gentiles: Christianity. They target Europe's main trading center, where the Frisian king Aldigisl rules.—ahmetkozan

title: Wolf Children
description_full:
Hana, a young woman in a large, busy city, attends a university while also working part-time at a dry cleaner. One day, while at the university, she meets a tall, young man who doesn't attend the university. After conversing with him in multiple conversations, they begin dating.
Eventually, at night, the man reveals that he can transform into a wolf at will, something he worried would scare Hana off. It is revealed that the man is the last of his kind. In Hana's apartment, the two have sex. Hana becomes pregnant, and she gives birth to Yuki, a girl, in their own apartment, delivered by Hana and the man.
Hana becomes pregnant again and gives birth to a baby boy, whose name is Ame, on a rainy day in spring. That same day, the father mysteriously leaves and is found dead in a river while trying to hunt food for the babies.
Hana attempts raising the two children with the little savings left behind by the wolf man, but this becomes a problem when Yuki cannot control switching between her human and wolf form. Hana also attempts to conceal their wolf forms from the people in the city, but, with Yuki, this is also a problem. Yuki becomes very lively while Ame stays by his mother at all times.
After social workers try to check on the children (as they have never had vaccinations), Hana decides she has had enough and moves to the countryside away from prying neighbors.
Life in the countryside is difficult at first with plants dying within just days after being planted, with the little savings left and with the house in need of repairs. Yuki and Ame have adventures around the forest, chasing animals and playing around while Hana repairs the house. With Nirasaki's help, the plants begin to grow into potatoes. Due to the large harvest, the people around exchange much-needed items for potatoes. Neighbors begin to visit and wonder why Hana's field grew crops successfully as all the other crops were destroyed by a boar.
In the winter, Yuki and Ame explore the terrain with Hana slowly following. Ame attempts catching a kingfisher before falling into a river. Yuki rescues him shortly after as Hana then sees Ame, lying there, motionless. Hana then hugs him as Ame then says that she's holding him too tight.
Yuki finally begins school at age 5 by following every direction Hana gives her, including a promise that Yuki doesn't transform into a wolf. Yuki is nervous at first but becomes less so as the day goes on. Yuki eventually passes up school, making friends. Eventually, they freak out due to the odd, frightening things Yuki collects, such as bones and dried reptiles.
Yuki vows to be more graceful and ladylike to get along with her friends, including a blue dress Hana makes for her to wear to school. Ame also attends but doesn't last long in school as he is bullied.
Hana becomes a nature conservationist but is paid little which is no problem to her. Ame accompanies her, visiting the old timber wolf and occasionally transforming into a wolf in front of her.
Years pass until Yuki is in the 4th grade. A transfer student whose name is Sohei figures out that something is up with Yuki. One day, while being continuously followed by Sohei, Yuki becomes angry, transforms into her wolf form and cuts his ear. Her class suspect that Yuki attacked him, and Yuki becomes upset by this.
Yuki doesn't attend school for many days while Sohei visits daily, giving her homework and food he gathers. Yuki refuses to see him. Meanwhile, Sohei says that a wolf attacked him, letting Yuki go of the blame. After a few more visits, they become friends, and Yuki attends.
Ame begins to travel into the mountains frequently, visiting a fox that is the leader of the forest which Ame calls Sensei. After a heated argument between Yuki and Ame over whether they are human or wolf. They fight each other in wolf form, causing quite a bit of destruction to the house as Hana tries to stop them. She realizes they are going on separate paths from each other.
A large amount of storms occur which makes Ame worried that something bad will happen to the forest. Ame begins visiting the mountains more frequently. When he returns, Ame reveals Sensei's leg is hurt, he might die and Ame might take over Sensei's responsibilities. Hana pleads him to stay home. She does this again when Yuki leaves for school.
Due to a very large storm passing by, the children get out of classes early and wait for their parents to pick them. One by one, they are picked up except for four kids, two of which are Yuki and Sohei. While searching for cards, Sohei falls asleep in class and Yuki tries to find him. The two others are left behind and then are picked up by the principal in the school car.
Ame leaves Hana at the house, and Hana tries finding him with no success, falling into puddles and sliding down hills. Meanwhile, Sohei and Yuki hide in a classroom. Sohei reveals that his mom got married and that she is pregnant. He says that once it's born, he wouldn't be needed anymore and that he would run away from home, becoming a boxer or wrestler. Yuki also reveals to Sohei something: that she was the wolf who attacked him. Sohei already knew this, however and told no one. He keeps his promise to not tell anyone, and Yuki thanks him.
Hana is sleeping in the forest. She has a dream that she visits her wolf man in a field filled with flowers. He tells her that she has raised the children well and that Ame is an adult. In the real world, Ame is carrying Hana to an abandoned parking lot, and it is still raining. Ame sets her down, and Hana wakes up. Hana pleads for him to come back, but Ame refuses, transforming into a wolf. The wolf runs off as Hana watches. It reaches the highest point on a mountain side and howls for a long time. Because of this, the sun begins to re-emerge. Ame stops howling and runs off while Hana says goodbye.
Two years later and shown in photos, Yuki leaves the house for the dorms in junior high school. It is revealed that Hana is still living in the house in the countryside. She is shown dipping a kebab of meat in a sauce then putting it in a small bowl next to the driver's license of the man she had had dated all those years ago.

title: The Battle of Jangsari
description_full: The story of Jangsari Landing Operation, 772 student soldiers - whose average age was 17 and who received just 2 weeks of boot camp training - were tossed into Korean War effort in order to pave the way for Incheon Landing Operation, which turned the tide of war.—AnonymusB

title: Flow: For Love of Water
description_full: Water is the very essence of life. It sustains every living being on this planet and without it, there would be nothing. Literally. In her film FLOW: For Love Of Water, director Irena Salina sounds the alarm: our life- giving water is a resource in peril across the planet. The film highlights the local intimacies of a global crisis: African struggle plumbers reconnecting shanty town water pipes under cover of darkness to ensure a community—Anonymous

title: Disturbing the Peace
description_full: A small-town marshal who hasn't carried a gun since he left the Texas Rangers after a tragic shooting, must pick up his gun again to battle with a gang of outlaw bikers that has invaded the town to pull off a brazen and violent heist.

title: 24 Little Hours
description_full: Fresh out on the streets from a 10-year prison sentence, a killer is focused on seeking vengeance against his beloved sister's murderers. Aided by those he believes he can trust, they go on a 24 hour killing spree to settle all scores as a discredited detective, whose superior questions her every move must deal with her past before she can uncover the shocking truth behind their motives.—Charles Fyffe

title: Intrigo: Death of an Author
description_full: A small open boat ploughs through a troubled sea off the Dutch coast. One solitary man at the rudder. A few days later, when the wind has settled, the smashed up remains of the boat will be found a few kilometres to the south. Meanwhile in Stockholm. David is contacted by his publisher. A manuscript by the famous author Germund Rein has turned up at the publishing house. David has translated the earlier works of Rein and is now given first option to tackle this one. However the manuscript has arrived in Sweden cloaked in strange circumstances. It has not been published in its country of origin. This is the original manuscript and it is accompanied by a letter which states that under no circumstances must the book be printed in its initial language. David also learns that the author Germund Rein has taken his own life by attaching a weight to his body and disappearing into the depths of the Atlantic. The letter must have been the last thing he wrote before he ended it all. The assignment takes David to Amsterdam. He finds parallels to his own life in Rein's novel. To his vanished wife Ewa, who according to the police most likely lost her life in Graues in the Austrian Alps some years earlier. But nothing is as it seems. The past will inevitably catch up. Guilt mixed with revenge. Germund Rein's fiction becomes reality. Finally David is forced to confront the uncomfortable truth. Maybe he actually failed to finish off Ewa that day in Graues after all?—D&D

title: Alone
description_full: "Alone" follows a writer seeking peace and solitude in the countryside in an attempt to recover from tragedy and finish her book. However, as the welcoming country house turns into a living hell, she soon realizes that her inner demons are not the worst of her problems.

title: Dark Waters
description_full: Cincinnati, Ohio 1998: Up-and-coming corporate attorney Robert Bilott, a new partner at a prestigious law firm, is visited by one of his grandmother's neighbors from West Virginia. Angry farmer Wilbur O. Tennant asks him to sue chemical multinational DuPont. His cows, according to the accusation, are being poisoned by a nearby landfill. Such a mandate is actually out of the question for Bilott, because he normally represents corporations. When he drives to remote Parkersburg to see for himself, his mind changes abruptly. The lawyer sees shocking evidence of the poisoning of the cattle with his own eyes: black teeth, huge tumors and terrible deformities. With the backing of his law firm boss Tom Terp, he files a lawsuit and gains access to confidential company files. While DuPont routinely plays for time, Bilott uncovers a scandal that is also endangering the health of many people. Much to his wife's chagrin, the idealistic lawyer gets stuck in the case, putting his career and health at risk. And yet he doesn't give up.—ADR Das Erste

title: Gog
description_full: Scientists working on induced hibernation for space travel are killed, apparently by machines acting independently. Security agent Sheppard arrives at the secret underground space research base to investigate possible sabotage. He finds that the whole base is coordinated by supercomputer NOVAC and its robots Gog and Magog; and a strange aircraft is detected high overhead.—Rod Crawford

title: Float Like a Butterfly
description_full: From the producers of "Once" and "Sing Street", "Float Like a Butterfly" is a powerful, timely story of a girl's fight for freedom and belonging. In a gender-reversal of the classic film "Billy Elliott," 15-year-old Frances must fight for the right to fight back. Raised in roadside camps in rural Ireland, Frances wants to champion her people inside the boxing ring and out, like her idol Muhammad Ali. But society is determined to break her spirit and destroy her way of life. And her father, once her greatest ally, is too defeated himself to imagine anything better for his daughter. But Frances was not born to be broken. In the mother of all fights, she must dig deep to find in herself the Champion her father once knew her to be.—WestEnd Films

title: Downhill
description_full: Public schoolboy Roddy Berwick is expelled from school when he takes the blame for a friend's charge and his life falls apart in a series of misadventures.—Col Needham

title: Epiphany
description_full: A young girl struggles to create a relationship with her father after the death of her aunt who raised her.

title: The Host
description_full: A chance opportunity arises for Robert Atkinson, a London banker who risks his bank's money to leave the mundane behind and start a new life. To take advantage, he unwittingly signs up with a Chinese cartel to transport a briefcase to Amsterdam. But all is not as it seems in a city veiled by dark secrets. Fuelled by power players, drugs, seduction and violence, Robert awaits his turn in a deadly game of choice and consequence.

title: The Big Mouth
description_full: While fishing on a San Diego beach, Gerald Clamson catches ... a sea diver! Even more weird, the "fish" resembles him. The man, who is not (yet) dead, reveals his secret to the peaceful angler: he is in fact a mobster who has cheated his associates out of their diamonds. What does not help Gerald at all is that the other hoods are persuaded HE is the double-crosser they are supposed to have done away with. Will he get himself out of such a tight situation? He will of course, but not without a little help from Suzie, the girl he only has eyes for!—Guy Bellinger

title: Undercover Hooligan
description_full: Known for his brutally violent policing tactics, suspended police officer Michael Clarke is sent undercover to infiltrate the notorious London criminal enterprise of Terance Turner, with the task of bringing the gang boss to justice.

title: Iceman
description_full: An anthropologist who is part of an arctic exploration team discovers the body of a prehistoric Neanderthal man who is subsequently resuscitated. The researcher must then decide what to do with the prehistoric man and he finds himself defending the man from those that want to dissect him in the name of science.—K. Rose

title: A Dog Called Money
description_full: As imaginative as the creative process it documents, A DOG CALLED MONEY is a uniquely intimate journey through the inspiration, writing and recording of a PJ Harvey record. Writer and musician Harvey and award-winning photographer Seamus Murphy, hatched a collaboration. Seeking first-hand experience of the countries she wanted to write about, Harvey accompanied Murphy on some of his worldwide reporting trips, joining him in Afghanistan, Kosovo, and Washington DC. Harvey collected words, Murphy collected images. Back home, the words become poems, songs, then an album, which is recorded in an unprecedented art experiment in Somerset House, London. In a specially constructed room behind one-way glass, the public - all cameras surrendered - are invited to watch the 5 week process as a live sound-sculpture. Murphy exclusively documents the experiment with the same forensic vision and private access as their travels. By capturing the immediacy of their encounters with the people and places they visited, Murphy shows the humanity at the heart of the work, tracing the sources of the songs, their special metamorphosis into recorded music, and, ultimately, cinema.

title: Medicine Man
description_full: An eccentric scientist working for a large drug company is working on a research project in the Amazon jungle. He sends for a research assistant and a gas chromatograph because he's close to a cure for cancer. When the assistant turns out to be a "mere woman", he rejects her help. Meanwhile, the bulldozers get closer to the area in which they are conducting research, and they eventually learn to work together, and begin to fall in love.—Ed Sutton

title: The Hobbit
description_full: Bilbo Baggins the Hobbit was just minding his own business, when his occasional visitor Gandalf the Wizard drops in one evening . One by one, a whole group of dwarves drop in, and before he knows it, Bilbo has joined their quest to reclaim their kingdom, taken from them by an evil dragon named Smaug. The only problem is that Gandalf has told the dwarves that Bilbo is an expert burglar, but he isn't....—Murray Chapman

title: Ernesto's Manifesto
description_full: Ernesto is a sweet, gentle man who is doing the best he can to get by in current-day Los Angeles. A sudden series of bad breaks, however, cause him to lose his job, his girlfriend, and his home - placing him in a very precarious situation. Then, just when all seems hopeless, he gains employment, a great place to live, an important friendship, and unexpectedly, an improved career trajectory. In his new position, he finds love, financial independence and a bright future - a happy ending beyond his wildest expectations.

title: Piranha
description_full: An insurance investigator and her local guide search the Lost River Lake area to find too missing teenagers. When stumbling on an abandoned military facility, they release by accident in the river some flesh-eating piranhas that were bred to use in the Vietnam war. The piranhas are heading straight to a nearby summer resort's lake and its guests.

title: Sorry We Missed You
description_full: Ricky and his family have been fighting an uphill struggle against debt since the 2008 financial crash. An opportunity to wrestle back some independence appears with a shiny new van and the chance to run a franchise as a self employed delivery driver. It's hard work, and his wife's job as a carer is no easier. The family unit is strong but when both are pulled in different directions everything comes to breaking point.

Before leaving, his doctor asks him to take a package to a friend of his. Without Stig-Helmer knowing it, the package contains 50,000 SEK, which is illegal to take out of the country. title: Holiday
description_full: Free-thinking Johnny Case finds himself betrothed to a millionaire's daughter. When her family, with the exception of black-sheep Linda and drunken Ned, want Johnny to settle down to big business, he rebels, wishing instead to spend the early years of his life on "holiday." With the help of his friends Nick and Susan Potter, he makes up his mind as to which is the better course, and the better mate.—Terri A. Mabry

title: House of Demons
description_full: Four estranged friends reunite and spend the night in a remote country house that was once home to a Manson Family like cult. As the night goes on, the strange rituals in the house's past open connections between the past, the present and the subconscious, forcing all the characters to confront their deepest secrets and darkest demons, or be destroyed by them. It's a blend of The Shining style freaky horror with the emotional character focus of a film like Magnolia. The film stars a number of prominent geek culture personalities including Amber Benson (Buffy the Vampire Slayer), Chloe Dykstra (Heroes of Cosplay), Tiffany Smith (DC All Access), etc.

title: A Serial Killer's Guide to Life
title_english: A Serial Killer's Guide to Life
title_long: A Serial Killer's Guide to Life (2019)
description_full: Lou Farnt is a meek young Englishwoman with poor self-esteem, who is emotionally browbeaten by her harsh and demanding mother, with whom she lives. Wanting something better, Lou follows the teachings of various self-help gurus, but especially that of Chuck Knoah. At a different self-hep guru's lecture, Lou sees a middle-aged women who strikes her attention. But when she looks again, the woman is gone. She later meets the woman, who introduces herself as Val Stone, a self-help teacher who believes she would be perfect for Lou. A day later, at Val's invitation, Lou visits her at a caravan park. There, Lou describes a road trip of discovery she is taking the next day, and insinuates that Lou should join her. Despite being flattered by the attention, Lou initially can't bring herself to leave home for an extended time for the first time. But her mother's emotional abusiveness changes her mind. The next day, Lou leaves with Val in a car, for the purpose of visiting various types of self-help gurus for research. A radio briefly mentions that a woman has been found murdered at a caravan park.With Val periodically leaving voice mails to let her mom know she is alright, they make their first stop at a wilderness retreat led by Ben. After engaging in some activities such as tree hugging, pitching camping tests and listening to one of the three other attendees provide evening entertainment by singing a song in Welsh, they all turn in. The next morning, Val hurries up Lou to leave. After they do so, we see the dead bodies of Ben and the attendees, their heads bashed in.The next stop is a "sonic vibration" retreat, where Lou and Val are the only two attendees of the husband-and-wife couple who run it at their large house. The following morning, Val knifes the wife to death, with Lou witnessing the aftermath. The husband stumbles onto the scene and tries to escape into the yard, but Val, wielding a knife, catches him. The two struggle, and Val is being overpowered when Lou kills the husband. Lou and Val leave their car behind and take the couple's minivan.As radio news begins reporting about the murders, Lou has Val pull over in order to throw up in a field. Val goes to her, and Lou angrily wrestles with her and soon has Val in a choke hold. Val urges Lou to kill her. But Lou cannot, and the two lay exhausted in the field. Val calls Lou the best student she's ever had.They visit a laugh-therapy workshop and murder the members. Then during a visit to a birth-memory guru, Lou, while Val waits in the hall, begins to hallucinate. She has a memory of herself killing her mother before leaving on this trip, with the image inter-cutting with that of Val murdering her mother.The two finally arrive at Chuck Knoah's estate. They find him a pathetic wreck, going through a terrible divorce and about to be dropped by his publisher for having no new book ideas. Ironically, once Knoah realizes these are the two serial killers on the news, he says his publisher would just love their memoirs, and is on a phone call arranging a meeting when Val shoots him in the head. Lou knifes Val, who earlier had called the police in an attempt to frame Lou and escape. A gun-wielding Val chases Lou to the edge of a cliff, and there they have a final meeting-of-the-minds as police sirens and a helicopter close in. Val shoots herself and the two fall on the grass. But moments later, when police arrive, Val seems to have vanished. The film ends with a repeat of the opening scene of Lou, walking outdoors, wearing earbuds and listening to a recorded Knoah lecture.(copied from Wikipedia)

title: Seance on a Wet Afternoon
description_full: Myra and Billy Savage are a married couple living in London. Myra works as a medium, who holds weekly meetings, séances, for a regular group of customers, while Billy supports her in these ventures, as he does not otherwise work, due to his asthma. "Arthur" is her spirit guide, who was their stillborn son. Myra is the dominant in the couple, Billy, the weak-minded follower. Myra, with Billy's support, devises a scheme to raise her public prominence as a medium: kidnap Amanda Clayton, the young daughter of a wealthy couple, and using her psychic powers provide information to the Claytons and the police of Amanda and the requested ransom money's whereabouts. Myra and Billy view this scheme as a victimless crime, if a crime at all, as they don't plan on harming Amanda, and they are returning the requested ransom. To carry out the scheme successfully, they will have to: kidnap Amanda; convince Amanda that her temporary captivity is not out of the ordinary, while having her not be able to identify them; insert Myra into the case of Amanda's kidnapping, her information which will be the key to finding Amanda and the money; and return Amanda and the money without having either traced back to them. Beyond these logistics, Myra and Billy themselves will factor into how the plan works. Myra may have either conscious or subconscious thoughts on what she wants to do, in her belief that she truly does have the power.—Huggo

title: Cottonpickin' Chickenpickers
description_full: Darby Clyde Fenster and Jerry Martin are a pair of penniless nincompoop-drifters who hop a freight and theyre on their way to Florida. Here is where our intrepid heroes find themselves facing one comic situation after another in this gloriously loopy Southern fried comedy-with-music. Their troubles only begin when they pass by a chicken farm and are overtaken by their pangs of hunger. The sneak into the hen house and haplessly attempt to nab some birds. This does not endear them to the farms owners and what comes next is positively too goofy to describe! The film is crammed with a pleasing blend of down-home humor and finger-popping country music. Sonny Tufts, whose reputation was ruined because of his fondness for the bottle, parodies himself in his role as the moonshine-swigging Cousin Urie (and mercifully ends his Hollywood career with this film). Boxing champ/movie comic Slapsie Maxie Rosenbloom appears as an ex-prizefighter-turned-mailman who is aptly described as "the prize dingaling of all time."—Anonymous

title: Terminator: Dark Fate
description_full: A young female Mexican worker, Dani Ramos, is hunted down by a virtually indestructible terminator from the future called a REV-9. However, she is protected by an enhanced human named Grace who is also from the future. They flee from the unstoppable terminator and, out of the blue, Sarah Connor helps them on the road. All three head to Laredo, Texas, where Grace has the coordinates of a possible support and where they meet a T-800 who is living in an isolated location with his family. The group teams up to try to destroy the REV-9.—Claudio Carvalho, Rio de Janeiro, Brazil

title: A Faithful Man
description_full: Marianne leaves Abel for Paul, his best friend and the father of her unborn child. Eight years later, Paul dies and Marianne returns to Abel. However, things have changed for the both of them and feelings of jealousy surround their new relationship.—AnonymusB

title: Waitress
description_full: Jenna is unhappily married, squirreling away money, and hoping to win a pie-baking contest so, with the prize money, she'll have enough cash to leave her husband Earl. She finds herself pregnant, which throws her plans awry. She bakes phenomenal pies at Joe's diner, listens to old Joe's wisdom, tolerates her sour boss Cal, is friends with Dawn and Becky (her fellow waitresses), and finds a mutual attraction with the new doctor in town. As the pregnancy advances, life with Earl seems less tolerable, a way out less clear, and the affair with the doctor complicated by his marriage. What options does a waitress have?—

title: Fright
description_full: Young babysitter Amanda arrives at the Lloyd residence to spend the evening looking after their young son. Soon after the Lloyds leave, a series of frightening occurrences in the gloomy old house have Amanda's nerves on edge. The real terror begins, however, when the child's biological father appears after recently escaping from a nearby mental institution.—Kevin Steinhauer

title: Blood Widow
description_full: A serial killer is terrorizing Arizona with the police in hot pursuit. What the police don't know is that a mysterious group are also pursuing the same killer to stop the killer from unleasing an evil like nothing before. From Vampires to Biblical wrath - everything comes down to one showdown!

title: Hotwired in Suburbia
description_full: A widowed mother must help her teenage daughter escape a life of crime after she becomes embroiled in a dangerous scheme to steal luxury cars for her high school teacher.

title: Angels Fallen
description_full: After the tragic loss of his wife battling the forces of darkness, Gabriel is persuaded to rejoin his former team of demon hunters traveling from relatively obscurity in America to the deep unknown regions of Europe. He is joined by his estranged best friend Michael who harbors a dark secret, the mystical Hannah whose visions predict the future, and a motley crew of demon slayers. After losing part of his team Gabriel must confront his tragic past and decide who really is friend or foe.

title: Motherless Brooklyn
description_full: Set against the backdrop of 1950s New York, "Motherless Brooklyn" follows Lionel Essrog (Norton), a lonely private detective afflicted with Tourette's Syndrome, as he ventures to solve his friend's murder. Armed only with a few clues and the powerful engine of his obsessive mind, Lionel unravels closely-guarded secrets that hold the fate of the whole city in the balance.—Warner Bros.

title: Harriet
description_full: Based on the thrilling and inspirational life of an iconic American freedom fighter, Harriet tells the extraordinary tale of Harriet Tubman's escape from slavery and transformation into one of America's greatest heroes. Her courage, ingenuity, and tenacity freed hundreds of slaves and changed the course of history.—Focus Features

title: World Gone Wild
description_full: In the nuclear ravaged wasteland of Earth 2087 water is as precious as life itself. The isolated Lost Wells outpost survived the holocaust and the inhabitants guard the source of their existence. Now an evil cult of renegades want control of their valuable water supply. And the villagers are no match for such brute military force. Only one man can help the stricken community - a mercenary living in a distant cannibal city. But even he, and his strange henchmen, may not be able to survive in the world gone wild.—

title: Mobile Suit Gundam Thunderbolt: Bandit Flower
title_english: Mobile Suit Gundam Thunderbolt: Bandit Flower
title_long: Mobile Suit Gundam Thunderbolt: Bandit Flower (2017)
description_full: Universal Century 0080, eight months after the One Year War, an Earth Federation spaceship is tasked to retrieve the Pyscho Zaku from the hands of the South Seas Alliance, a cult that makes its followers sacrifice their limbs to control the mobile suits. To the spaceship's aid is the Atlas Gundam, a new amphibious mobile suit piloted by Io Fleming. Meanwhile, Daryl Lorenz joins the Zeon Remnants on Earth whose mission is also to retrieve the Psycho Zaku.—heyitsnuel

title: Western Stars
description_full: Live concert performance of Bruce Springsteen singing songs from his album 'Western Stars'.

title: Move Over, Darling
description_full: Three years into their loving marriage with two infant daughters at home in Los Angeles, Nicholas Arden and Ellen Wagstaff Arden are on a plane that goes down in the South Pacific. Although most passengers manage to survive the incident, Ellen presumably perishes when she is swept off the lifeboat she is on. Her body is not recovered. Fast forward five years. Nicky, wanting now to move on with his life, has Ellen declared legally dead. Part of that moving on includes getting remarried, this time to a young woman named Bianca Steele, who, for their honeymoon, he plans to take to the same Monterrey resort where he and Ellen spent their honeymoon. On that very same day, Ellen is dropped off in Los Angeles by the Navy, who rescued her from the South Pacific island where she was stranded for the past five years. She asked the Navy not to publicize her rescue or notify Nicky as she wanted to do so herself. Upon arrival back home, a shocked Grace Arden, Nicky's mother, informs Ellen that Nicky just got married that morning and that she, as his true wife as opposed to Bianca being his bride, should go to Monterrey to tell Nicky she's alive. She does so. Although Nicky is equally as shocked as his mother was when he sees Ellen for the first time, it places him in a difficult position. Although he loves Ellen and wants more than anything to be with her, he has Bianca's feelings to take into consideration. As such, he finds it difficult to tell Bianca, who is in a honeymoon amorous mood. Nicky's inability to tell Bianca irks Ellen, who believes it is a manifestation of his love for Bianca over her. Nicky, however, ends up with questions of his own about Ellen's faithfulness and love for him when he learns that Ellen was not all alone on that island but with a handsome man named Stephen Burkett, the two who pet nicknamed each other Adam and Eve. Nicky's questions about her faithfulness increase when she purposefully withholds information about Stephen from him.—Huggo

title: The Thief Lord
description_full: A tale about two young boys, Prosper and Bo, who flee to Venice after being orphaned and dumped in the care of a cruel auntie. Hiding in the canals and alleyways of the city, the boys are befriended by a gang of young urchins and their enigmatic leader, the Thief Lord. From their home base of an old cinema theater, the children steal from the rich to support themselves and soon capture the interest of a bumbling detective. However, a greater threat to the children is something from a forgotten past-- a beautiful magical treasure with the power to spin time itself.—Kasey and Toby

title: L'Atalante
description_full: When Juliette marries Jean, she comes to live with him as he captains a river barge. Besides the two of them, are a cabin boy and the strange old second mate, Pere Jules. Soon bored by life on the river, she slips off to see the nightlife when they land at Paris. Angered by this, Jean sets off, leaving Juliette behind. Overcome by grief and longing for his wife, Jean falls into a depression and Pere Jules goes searching for Juliette.—dlevy1201

title: A Dash of Love
description_full: When an aspiring chef lands an assistant job at her idol's restaurant, she's convinced her big break is just around the corner. After a rocky start, she befriends the handsome executive chef and they begin bonding in the kitchen. But her joy is short lived when she discovers her female boss is stealing her recipes and fires them both to protect her secret. Together, they set out to create their own pop-up restaurant and discover the most important ingredient is love.—Happy_Evil_Dude

title: Ginger Snaps Back: The Beginning
description_full: Set in 19th Century Canada, Brigette and her sister Ginger take refuge in a Traders' Fort which later becomes under siege by some savage werewolves. And an enigmatic Indian hunter decides to help the girls, but one of the girls has been bitten by a werewolf. Brigitte and Ginger may have no one to turn to but themselves.—Wallace Entertainment
